--------- To test a Terminating Gateway connecting to an external service using mutual TLS (mTLS), you need to simulate both ends of the connection. 
The Terminating Gateway acts as the client, and your external service (static-server) acts as the server. 
Both will need certificates signed by a common Certificate Authority (CA).
Run the below commands on your local machine to generate the root CA, the external server's certificate, and the Terminating Gateway's client certificate.

1. Generate the Root CA
# Create CA private key and certificate
openssl req -x509 -newkey rsa:4096 -days 365 -nodes \
  -keyout ca.key -out ca.crt -subj "/CN=MyLocalCA"

2. Generate the Server Certificate (for static-server)
# Create Server private key and CSR (Certificate Signing Request)
openssl req -newkey rsa:2048 -nodes \
  -keyout server.key -out server.csr -subj "/CN=static-server"

# Sign the Server CSR with the Root CA
openssl x509 -req -in server.csr -days 365 \
  -CA ca.crt -CAkey ca.key -CAcreateserial -out server.crt

3. Generate the Client Certificate (for Terminating Gateway)
# Create Client private key and CSR
openssl req -newkey rsa:2048 -nodes \
  -keyout client.key -out client.csr -subj "/CN=terminating-gateway"

# Sign the Client CSR with the Root CA
openssl x509 -req -in client.csr -days 365 \
  -CA ca.crt -CAkey ca.key -CAcreateserial -out client.crt

% ls -lrt
-rw-------@ 1 abhineet  staff  3272  8 May 10:26 ca.key
-rw-r--r--@ 1 abhineet  staff  1805  8 May 10:26 ca.crt
-rw-------@ 1 abhineet  staff  1704  8 May 10:27 server.key
-rw-r--r--@ 1 abhineet  staff   895  8 May 10:27 server.csr
-rw-r--r--@ 1 abhineet  staff  1444  8 May 10:27 server.crt
-rw-------@ 1 abhineet  staff  1704  8 May 10:28 client.key
-rw-r--r--@ 1 abhineet  staff   903  8 May 10:28 client.csr
-rw-r--r--@ 1 abhineet  staff    41  8 May 10:28 ca.srl
-rw-r--r--@ 1 abhineet  staff  1452  8 May 10:28 client.crt

---------------- Create Kubernetes Secrets for the Certs -----------------
1. Secret for the External Service:

kubectl create secret generic external-certs \
  --from-file=server.crt --from-file=server.key --from-file=ca.crt

2. Secret for the Terminating Gateway:

kubectl create secret generic tgw-client-certs \
  --from-file=client.crt --from-file=client.key --from-file=ca.crt
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
kubectl apply -f static-client.yaml
kubectl apply -f static-server.yaml
kubectl apply -f service-intentions.yaml
kubectl apply -f terminating-gateway.yaml
curl -k --request PUT --data @external-service.json --header "X-Consul-Token: 6eb8cb43-xxxxxxxxxxxx-34110ce139a5" https://localhost:8501/v1/catalog/register   (register external service in Consul catalog)
--------------------------------
Validation:-
kubectl exec -it static-client-74bc477bcd-svqqz -c static-client -- sh
/ # curl static-server.virtual.consul
Success! Connected via mTLS to the external server.
